The paper focuses on a natural language processing task of answering cloze-style questions over documents, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The model proposed in the paper uses a recurrent neural network and attention mechanism, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of different compositional operators for implementing the gated-attention, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
